Local and international experts will put their heads together to try to develop more effective treatment for MDR and XDR TB. CAPE TOWN - The fourth multidrug-resistant tuberculosis (MDR TB) conference will be held at the University of Cape Town (UCT) this weekend.Local and international experts will put their heads together to try to develop more effective treatment for MDR and XDR tuberculosis.Multi-drug resistant and extensively drug-resistant TB (XDR TB) places a huge burden on South Africa s health sector.Head of Groote Schuur Hospital s Pulmonology Department Professor Keertan Dheda says 20,000 multidrug-resistant TB cases were registered across the country in 2014. South Africa has the highest incidents of TB globally and it is now officially the most common cause of death in the country. The conference will also feature the launch of the Lancet Commission on drug-resistant TB.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)